#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:8
msgid ""
"This type implements the super weapon known from :game:`Tiberian Sun`, "
"with several extensions. It makes one or more buildings, called cannons, "
"of arbitrary type fire at the same time at either a target location "
"selected by the player or at themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:13
msgid ""
"The AI cannot make full use of this super weapon yet, because it does not"
" respect ranges, which is a fundamental feature of this super weapon "
"type."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:16
msgid "Default values for general tags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:21
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.RangeMinimum=float - cell range`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:19
msgid ""
"The minimum range below which a cannon is not eligible to fire. Set to "
"negative values to use each cannon's primary weapon's minimum range. "
"Defaults to :value:`0.0`, which disables the check."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:26
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.RangeMaximum=float - cell range`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:24
msgid ""
"The maximum range above which a cannon is not eligible to fire. Set to "
"negative values to use the each cannon's primary weapon's range. Defaults"
" to :value:`-1.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:30
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.MaxCount=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:29
msgid ""
"The maximum number of cannons firing. Set to negative values for "
"unlimited cannons. Defaults to :value:`1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:35
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]SW.AITargeting=enumeration`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:33
msgid ""
"AI does not respect ranges. For :tag:`EMPulse.TargetSelf=yes` super "
"weapons, use :value:`NoTarget` to enable AI players to use it. Defaults "
"to :value:`None`."
msgstr ""

