msgid ""
"Used when there is no cannon in range. Defaults to "
":value:`AttackOutOfRange`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:43
msgid "EMPulse specific tags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:48
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]EMPulse.Cannons=list of BuildingType`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:46
msgid ""
"The building types considered to check the range and to fire. If the list"
" is empty, all buildings with :tag:`EMPulseCannon=yes` are considered. "
"All buildings are required to have a primary weapon. Defaults to "
":value:`none`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:54
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]EMPulse.TargetSelf=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:51
msgid ""
"Whether each cannon to fire should fire its primary weapon at itself. The"
" cannon does not actually fire; the weapon just detonates once on the "
"cannon building immediately, similar to a death weapon. To actually "
"damage itself, the building needs to have :tag:`DamageSelf=yes` set. "
"Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:61
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]EMPulse.Linked=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:57
msgid ""
"Whether only one cannon needs to satisfy the range checks to the target. "
"All other cannons will then be considered regardless of range. Only makes"
" sense if :tag:`SW.MaxCount` has a value other than :value:`1`. The "
"difference to just making the cannon itself a designator is that the "
"cannon can be made to not provide fire clearance on their own. Defaults "
"to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:66
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]EMPulse.PulseBall=Animation`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:64
msgid ""
"The optional animation played at the FLH at the beginning of the delay "
"before the cannon fires. Use :value:`none` to disable the pulse ball. "
"This does not disable the delay. Defaults to :value:`PULSBALL`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:70
msgid ":tagdef:`[SuperWeapon]EMPulse.PulseDelay=integer - frames`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:69
msgid ""
"The delay before firing, but after the cannon rotated towards the target "
"and started the :tag:`EMPulse.PulseBall` animation. Defaults to "
":value:`32`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:72
msgid ""
"There are three firing modes opposed to the one known from "
":game:`Tiberian Sun`. Buildings with :tag:`EMPulseCannon=yes` rotate "
"their turret and then create a single bullet using the primary weapon "
"that is thrown at the target. The building does not actually fire and "
"several weapon and building effects are not respected that apply when the"
" building is on a regular attack mission."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:78
msgid ""
"If :tag:`EMPulse.TargetSelf=yes`, a single bullet is immediately "
"detonated at each firing cannon's location. Again, the building does not "
"actually fire."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:81
msgid ""
"If a building with :tag:`EMPulseCannon=no` is put into "
":tag:`EMPulse.Cannons`, the building will fire its primary weapon at the "
"target directly, but without charging or turret rotation, and without any"
" further range checks. Thus, turrets are not supported, and buildings are"
" not guaranteed to fire at all if they didn't rotate in the right "
"direction before the super weapon is fired."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:87
msgid "Other changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/superweapons/types/empulse.rst:89
msgid ""
"The pulse ball animation that was previously hardcoded to "
":value:`PULSBALL` has now been made customizable and optional. If an "
":tag:`EMPulseCannon=yes` building had a primary weapon without any valid "
":tag:`Report` set, the game would crash. This does not happen anymore."
msgstr ""

